narratives.question_text: How would you summarize ECON 110 05 for a fellow student? Would you recommend ECON 110 05 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: It was a good learning experience.
Great class to improve speaking and listening skills.

The hype is true: Sebastin Daz is definitely who you want to take this course with. It's a formula class, so all the sections cover the same stuff, but Sebastin legitimately cares about his students. He's fun and funny; I definitely recommend taking this course with him.

I would recommend it to them only if they needed it to fulfill a distributional requirement or if they were trying to become fluent in the language. In other words, I would only recommend it if they needed to take it. Otherwise, I wouldn't, because it is pretty boring and only got more tedious as the semester went along.
